Abstract = {{Like illness-inducing agents (e.g., lithium chloride), drugs of abuse
   also suppress intake of a taste solution. To explore the nature of this
   drug-induced intake reduction, in the current study three aqueous
   stimuli with different initial values served as the conditioned stimuli
   (CSs) that were paired with a standard dose of amphetamine in a
